commit_message:
Use oslo.log instead of oslo-incubator logging

log module has been removed from oslo-incubator after oslo.log was
released. This change will fail tests till a new guest image is built
with oslo.log in the requirements.txt file. The change
https://review.openstack.org/162676 has been submitted to get a new
guest image.

Implements: blueprint port-oslo-incubator-to-oslo-log
Depends-On: I1cb764c6bd978be71c5a9a6dd26d53ebea5192bb
Change-Id: I753573c14facf5bf916d6deee8c1cd7f112a9f48

commit_message:
Sync oslo-incubator

This should be the final sync of oslo-incubator pre-Kilo. Detailed
changelist follows.

_i18n.py

ba544bbc switch to oslo_i18n

eventlet_backdoor.py

7cc15017 Change oslo.config to oslo_config
875eb30d Remove oslo.log code and clean up versionutils API
c6863a5c Remove unnecessary import of eventlet

loopingcall.py

875eb30d Remove oslo.log code and clean up versionutils API

periodic_task.py

7cc15017 Change oslo.config to oslo_config
875eb30d Remove oslo.log code and clean up versionutils API
c9166a2f Allow overriding name for periodic tasks
4abeda60 Separate add_periodic_task from the metaclass __init__

service.py

4dcc8b35 Optimization of waiting subprocesses in ProcessLauncher
7cc15017 Change oslo.config to oslo_config
875eb30d Remove oslo.log code and clean up versionutils API
b888c0fa Merge "Added graceful argument on Service.stop method"
492fa4a3 Added graceful argument on Service.stop method
7ec3fab2 Remove extra white space in log message

systemd.py

875eb30d Remove oslo.log code and clean up versionutils API

threadgroup.py

875eb30d Remove oslo.log code and clean up versionutils API

versionutils.py

154263ae Add liberty release name to versionutils
fc6f2479 Switch from oslo.config to oslo_config
875eb30d Remove oslo.log code and clean up versionutils API

Other changes are to address the fact that periodic_task no longer
supports the ticks_between_runs argument.

Change-Id: Idf7899ead53c14c32dc343f2249f105e4b053209

subject: Write post job logs to apache and swift
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-07-29 19:45:12.000000000', 'files': ['jenkins/jobs/python-jobs.yaml'], 'message': "Write post job logs to apache and swift

Currently we don't get generated parent dir indexes for swift uploaded
logs. This is mostly ok for check/gate jobs as we address the log dirs
directly in the path supplied to gerrit and presented to users. For post
jobs we do not do this so rely on something to provide a proper index.
Go back to apache uploaded logs in addition to swift uploaded logs so
that these files will be indexed until we can set up indexing with
swift.

Change-Id: I7f688834e0d3ad91b81dcbde7643a4b5c208748e
"}]
commit_message:
Write post job logs to apache and swift

Currently we don't get generated parent dir indexes for swift uploaded
logs. This is mostly ok for check/gate jobs as we address the log dirs
directly in the path supplied to gerrit and presented to users. For post
jobs we do not do this so rely on something to provide a proper index.
Go back to apache uploaded logs in addition to swift uploaded logs so
that these files will be indexed until we can set up indexing with
swift.

Change-Id: I7f688834e0d3ad91b81dcbde7643a4b5c208748e

commit_message:
Rakefile: create a task to copy logs

When running beaker with Jenkins, it's useful to get the logs at the end
of the job, so we can easily debug eventual failures.

This patch aims to create a Rake task to copy the logs. For that, we
need to make sure WORKSPACE is set (automatically done when running the
job on a Jenkins node). This task will copy the Keystone logs in the workspace.

To run the task, you need to run `rake copy_logs` which is what
OpenStack Infra is doing.

Change-Id: I54550cbce7eb1eb0189e29481649aeb2525c8130

commit_message:
Publish capabilities after volume creation successful

Create several thin provisioned volumes within one minute,
if one volume size is larger than host's free_capacity_gb and
smaller than free_virtual, this creation will be successful,
but the next volume creation will be failed. Publishing service
capabilities after volume creation successful, this bug will
be fixed.

Change-Id: Id3e195d414056c6baeb2afc263d52c7af6290749
Closes-Bug: #1445398

commit_message:
Adds parameter specification for #call()

Adds 1st parameter specification to #call method so that
 1) $dict(key) will not lead to attempt to call dict
 2) it would be possible to implement custom #call versions
     (for example to make $dict(key) possible)

commit_message:

When function has *args parameter it is always the last positional
argument. In yaql it is possible to declare parameters by their
position rather than by the name. But for *args position number
it didn't worked as expected

commit_message:
add E006: check for lines longer than 79 columns

This mimics the widely accepted convention from PEP8 and many other
places that lines longer than 79 columns can not only cause problems
when reading/writing code, but also often indicate a bad smell,
e.g. too many levels of indentation due to overly complex functions
which require refactoring into smaller chunks.

Change-Id: Ic2532676e46e93f129d590d1fa7a044ef65f50fb

commit_message:
Add constraint of IntegerType maximum for API

Currently, the Ceilometer API has no constraint of maximum of int
type. That will cause error when a python unlimited int num
converted to C int type(as the bug described).

This change adds constraint of IntegerType maximum for API, including
period and evaluation_periods fields of alarm threshold_rule, and
search_offset query field.

Change-Id: If9afa1ce8ef31f45e80ef19b26e199c69b5ec26e
Closes-bug: #1315819
DocImpact

subject: Fix Keystone Auth and Tests
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-07-27 16:30:29.000000000', 'files': ['tests/auth/test_keystone.py', 'anchor/auth/keystone.py'], 'message': 'Fix Keystone Auth and Tests

Keystone Auth was previously non-functional as the Keystone
API resource being used does not support Roles as required
by the function to map to Anchor Groups.

This was further compounded by the required HTTP return code
being 200 (OK), but the function with POST returns a 201
(CREATED).

This change, switches to to using a GET Keystone API
resource to validate the token passed in by the user.

The keystone unit tests have been updated to a real sample
JSON response from the resource called (rather than the
bogus one previously used) and split up the 3 current tests
into separate functions.

However, long term I really think we will want to switch to
using keystonemiddleware library - rather than our homebrew
usage.

Change-Id: I7b8d81764934638040120bcefe81d012748007c8
Closes-Bug: #1478532
Signed-off-by: Dave Walker (Daviey) <email@daviey.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Fix Keystone Auth and Tests

Keystone Auth was previously non-functional as the Keystone
API resource being used does not support Roles as required
by the function to map to Anchor Groups.

This was further compounded by the required HTTP return code
being 200 (OK), but the function with POST returns a 201
(CREATED).

This change, switches to to using a GET Keystone API
resource to validate the token passed in by the user.

The keystone unit tests have been updated to a real sample
JSON response from the resource called (rather than the
bogus one previously used) and split up the 3 current tests
into separate functions.

However, long term I really think we will want to switch to
using keystonemiddleware library - rather than our homebrew
usage.

Change-Id: I7b8d81764934638040120bcefe81d012748007c8
Closes-Bug: #1478532
Signed-off-by: Dave Walker (Daviey) <email@daviey.com>

commit_message:
Add ability for GET path to see/select alternate frag archs

Changes include:
- storage nodes reporting when they have >1 fragment archive
available
- GET path recognizing alternates, when to use them and building
up the getters accordingly
- GET path assuring that even if it has enough FA's that they
all come from the same set (via etag) and if not try GETs from
the parity nodes to see if they have some more.  This addresses
the case where a simple overwrite PUT happens with a node off
and a subsequent GET comes in while its back but before it gets
updated with the latest stuff.
- associated test changes for existing code
- new unit tests and new probe tests

Co-Authored-By: Clay Gerrard <clay.gerrard@gmail.com>
Closes-Bug: 1457691
Change-Id: I2491edaa56dcf4eb9e864bbf263be8fa588d64c2

commit_message:
Retry ipmi commands unless the failure is not retriable

Consider that image deployment is a time-consuming operation, most
ipmi failures worth retrying, even when BMC is temporarily offline.
List keywords of error messages in configuration file, ipmi command
will be retried if runtime error message does not match keywords.

Change-Id: I444ec23a40bc044117699315c4d3257414a9d85b
Closes-Bug: 1474953

commit_message:
libvirt: Remove error messages from multipath command output before parsing

Changes the implementation of _get_multipath_device_name() to use
linuxscsi.find_multipath_device().
This fixes an issue in _get_multipath_device_name() that fails to
parse the output from 'multipath' command when the stdout contains
error messages in addition to the expected output.

Change-Id: I7af5c8c8c351e7921881cb3ece4e61280dc9a9b8
Closes-Bug: #1433204

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-07-16 13:39:41.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/db/migration/models/head.py', 'neutron/services/bgp_speaker/dr_rpc_base.py', 'etc/neutron.conf', 'neutron/db/migration/alembic_migrations/versions/15be73214821_add_bgp_speaker_model_data.py', 'neutron/db/dr_agentschedulers_db.py', 'neutron/services/bgp_speaker/plugin.py', 'neutron/extensions/dr_agentscheduler.py', 'neutron/common/constants.py', 'neutron/agent/dr_agent.py', 'neutron/tests/unit/services/bgp_speaker/test_bgp_speaker.py', 'neutron/tests/unit/extensions/test_bgp_speaker.py', 'etc/dr_agent.ini', 'neutron/scheduler/dr_agent_scheduler.py', 'neutron/common/topics.py', 'neutron/cmd/eventlet/agents/dr_agent.py', 'setup.cfg', 'etc/policy.json', 'neutron/tests/etc/policy.json'], 'message': '[WIP] BGP Dynamic Routing: adding agent and scheduling

Dynamic routing needs a new agent that will host the BGP speaker driver
and will do the actual communication between BGP peers.
This agent will take information from a single BGP speaker entity,
that has all the information that the agent needs to do the routing
exchange: peers and routes. In this approach, an agent can only host one
BGP speaker to avoid conflicts.
This commit intruduces a dummy agent that auto-registers to Neutron API
and send keep-alive messages.

A binding between the agent and the BGP speaker is mandatory in the
database and also the api endpoints to let the user
associate/disassociate a BGP speaker to an agent.
There is also an autoscheduling feature that will assign a BGP speaker
to the first agent that asks for synchronization. Default
scheduler class will only assign non-assigned BGP speakers to
agents.

HA feature (two agents hosting the same routing instance) has to be done manually.

Outstanding Items:
- Unit and API testcases
- RpcCallback implementation

Change-Id: Ib5ea27c477c0187cd81ea5f5307c83b712c003ff
Partially-Implements: blueprint bgp-dynamic-routing
Co-Authored-By: Ryan Tidwell <ryan.tidwell@hp.com>
Co-Authored-By: Jaume Devesa <devvesa@gmail.com>
'}]
commit_message:
[WIP] BGP Dynamic Routing: adding agent and scheduling

Dynamic routing needs a new agent that will host the BGP speaker driver
and will do the actual communication between BGP peers.
This agent will take information from a single BGP speaker entity,
that has all the information that the agent needs to do the routing
exchange: peers and routes. In this approach, an agent can only host one
BGP speaker to avoid conflicts.
This commit intruduces a dummy agent that auto-registers to Neutron API
and send keep-alive messages.

A binding between the agent and the BGP speaker is mandatory in the
database and also the api endpoints to let the user
associate/disassociate a BGP speaker to an agent.
There is also an autoscheduling feature that will assign a BGP speaker
to the first agent that asks for synchronization. Default
scheduler class will only assign non-assigned BGP speakers to
agents.

HA feature (two agents hosting the same routing instance) has to be done manually.

Outstanding Items:
- Unit and API testcases
- RpcCallback implementation

Change-Id: Ib5ea27c477c0187cd81ea5f5307c83b712c003ff
Partially-Implements: blueprint bgp-dynamic-routing
Co-Authored-By: Ryan Tidwell <ryan.tidwell@hp.com>
Co-Authored-By: Jaume Devesa <devvesa@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Delegate failure capturing to a object that is returned on run

This allows capturing of tracebacks and using the full logging
support when a non-process-pool executor is being used which makes
the handling of exceptions and there logging more natural (vs
just printing the traceback).

Change-Id: I40e7841f57209964f01a43a581504a309906b475

commit_message:
Allow providing a state-name translation dict

Certain projects use ``None`` as a state (and it is
possible for other projects to use other hashable
objects as states) so make it possible to provide
a renaming dict that can provide an alternative name
mapping.

This allows those projects to translate their states
into something useful on conversion.

Change-Id: I1debeaf0c1d7a7af58376ada50b014cf5de40746

commit_message:
Add response message when volume delete

When a request is send for deleting a volume it will not print any
success message if it deleted successfully.It will print only error
message if the volume deletion fails. This fix will print response
message if the volume deletion is success.

Change-Id: Icef2045107e1dcc3b7f2abfeb50b3f180ded1a27
Closes-Bug: #1475430

commit_message:

The job proved working in experimental pipeline, e.g.:
http://logs.openstack.org/22/194722/6/experimental/check-ironic-inspector-dsvm-nv/9ed2a9c/
(expected success) or
http://logs.openstack.org/44/202544/1/experimental/gate-ironic-inspector-dsvm-nv/1c1e49f/
(expected failure).

Now we can let it run on all changes (still non-voting).

Change-Id: I3926c42d1b4bdc36ee0fd93475454bc5a051597b

A regression was introduced to glance_store which affected its
use with ceph.  Ceph jobs are run for several projects, but not
requirements, therefore the regression was not noted when

Related-bug: #1475811'}]
commit_message:
Add ceph devstack job to requirements

A regression was introduced to glance_store which affected its
use with ceph.  Ceph jobs are run for several projects, but not
requirements, therefore the regression was not noted when
glance_store was released and the requirements uppper constraint
increased.  Run the ceph job on requirements changes.

Change-Id: I61a240817616d88863318b972edadfd67ea35d6c
Related-bug: #1475811

commit_message:
Add -n to tcpdump as part of net_probe

In order to prevent tcpdump from hanging due to no available DNS
servers, we need to add -n to command line parameters.

Closes-Bug: 1466020

commit_message:
Collect constraints

Common constraints like ISO_8601 should be collect in one common
path. Other client constraints should be separate from
other resources (like plugin) and put in the common directory as well if that
constraint did not use client at all.

blueprint collect-constraints

Change-Id: I4193884484ae25ff4f6331cf825ae501c8c11d6b

subject: Fix test_migrations on Python 3
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-07-28 10:50:06.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_db/sqlalchemy/test_migrations.py', 'oslo_db/tests/sqlalchemy/test_migrations.py'], 'message': 'Fix test_migrations on Python 3

migrate.versioning.api.VerNum() conversion to integer doesn't work in
all cases. Cast explicitly to int in WalkVersionsMixin.walk_versions()
to fix this issue.

Modify unit tests to use VerNum objects instead of using directly
integers. The bug was not seen in tests because tests used int numbers.

Example of error:

    Traceback (most recent call last):
      ...
      File "oslo_db/sqlalchemy/test_migrations.py", line 189, in walk_versions
        versions = range(self.INIT_VERSION + 1, self.REPOSITORY.latest + 1)
    TypeError: 'VerNum' object cannot be interpreted as an integer

This bug impact for example glance.tests.unit.test_migrations of the
Glance project.

Change-Id: I043a66268b957b97f2e8f652c0ee8aec3a00e8dd
'}]
commit_message:
Fix test_migrations on Python 3

migrate.versioning.api.VerNum() conversion to integer doesn't work in
all cases. Cast explicitly to int in WalkVersionsMixin.walk_versions()
to fix this issue.

Modify unit tests to use VerNum objects instead of using directly
integers. The bug was not seen in tests because tests used int numbers.

Example of error:

    Traceback (most recent call last):
      ...
      File "oslo_db/sqlalchemy/test_migrations.py", line 189, in walk_versions
        versions = range(self.INIT_VERSION + 1, self.REPOSITORY.latest + 1)
    TypeError: 'VerNum' object cannot be interpreted as an integer

This bug impact for example glance.tests.unit.test_migrations of the
Glance project.

Change-Id: I043a66268b957b97f2e8f652c0ee8aec3a00e8dd

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-06-19 17:17:04.000000000', 'files': ['docker/centos/binary/cinder-data/Dockerfile'], 'message': "Access volume groups created by Cinder from the host

Cinder creates volume groups that can't be seen from the host unless
/etc/lvm is mounted into the data container.  When /etc/lvm is mounted,
the host is able to see the volumes Cinder creates, and delete
them when needed.  Also, Cinder volumes remain persistant while follow
container best practices.

Change-Id: I01ad0a20fe1ae7317069b3b567d18bba590b0a31
Closes-bug: #1460134
"}]
commit_message:
Access volume groups created by Cinder from the host

Cinder creates volume groups that can't be seen from the host unless
/etc/lvm is mounted into the data container.  When /etc/lvm is mounted,
the host is able to see the volumes Cinder creates, and delete
them when needed.  Also, Cinder volumes remain persistant while follow
container best practices.

Change-Id: I01ad0a20fe1ae7317069b3b567d18bba590b0a31
Closes-bug: #1460134

commit_message:
Update service helper scripts for variable changes

- Updated the required variables to be sorted so
  that they are better visible one on each line

- Removed variable defaults from each service scripts
  and added them to tools/genenv file which holds
  all default values

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-07-28 14:11:18.000000000', 'files': ['barbican/tests/api/test_resources_policy.py'], 'message': 'Flatten exceptions used in policy tests

The policy tests are meant to check if certain roles are properly
enforced by our policy engine. To do this we use the standard
controllers and force an exception in the actual code, just after we
have actually passed the policy.

The code was actually doing what it intended to do, in an unintended
way. By passing the "external_project_id" to the
on_[get|post|delete|put] it was finally getting a TypeError when it
would try to execute the actual code. This was unexpected and
confusing.

The intent of this CR is to get rid of the aforementioned behaviour and
instead force an IOError whenever possible (either by accessing certain
functions, or when trying to access the body of the request).

Change-Id: I98d168c1fe249c1fc5e5182cac43f63a07fa2e3a
'}]
commit_message:
Flatten exceptions used in policy tests

The policy tests are meant to check if certain roles are properly
enforced by our policy engine. To do this we use the standard
controllers and force an exception in the actual code, just after we
have actually passed the policy.

The code was actually doing what it intended to do, in an unintended
way. By passing the "external_project_id" to the
on_[get|post|delete|put] it was finally getting a TypeError when it
would try to execute the actual code. This was unexpected and
confusing.

The intent of this CR is to get rid of the aforementioned behaviour and
instead force an IOError whenever possible (either by accessing certain
functions, or when trying to access the body of the request).

Change-Id: I98d168c1fe249c1fc5e5182cac43f63a07fa2e3a

commit_message:
Fix roles and playbooks not putting deploy image on /httpboot

Due to latest changes, the image created by DIB is placed on
the folder you run ansible-playbook and it's not placed
on /httpboot.
This causes the deploy-dynamic top-level playbook to fail
since it can't find the image to boot.

Change-Id: I55ce1bd2a9686ff75d0199593e015012e8355fb5
Closes-Bug: 1478970

commit_message:
Preserve DVR FIP rule priority over Agent restarts

IP rule priorities assigned to DVR floating IPs need
to be preserved over L3 agent restarts. Such a
 mechanism is already in place for Link Local IP
address allocation.

This change generalizes the allocation management
mechanism used for managing Link Local IP addresses
and utilizes it for managing floating ip rule priorities.

An ItemAllocator class is defined and used to instantiate
allocators for floating ip rule priorities and Link Local
IP addresses.

Co-Authored-By: Adolfo Duarte <adolfo.duarte@hp.com>
Change-Id: Ia413e87fe614331ba59b528e64267049dc17173a

commit_message:
fuel-agent: use different md metadata version

0.90 will be used for centos only letting GRUB-legacy to boot.
Otherwise, default (1.2) will be used as GRUB2 is able to deal with it.

Change-Id: I89c5178d991970de4682c1e239e0ecb014ba61bd

commit_message:
Add tag to package and service resources

In order to be able to take an action after all the packages of the
module have been installed/updated or all the services have been
started/restarted, we set a 'ironic-package' and 'ironic-service' tag
for each package and service of this module.

At the moment, there is a generic openstack tag that is not specific
enough if one wants to take action upon a single module change.

Use case :

If an action needs to be taken after all the packages have been
installed or updated : Package <| tag == 'ironic-package' |> -> X

Change-Id: I7cea635625e841db05a5163e7b7ea5a138c3c307

commit_message:
Add tag to package and service resources

In order to be able to take an action after all the packages of the
module have been installed/updated or all the services have been
started/restarted, we set a 'gnocchi-package' and 'gnocchi-service'
tag for each package and service of this module.

At the moment, there is a generic openstack tag that is not specific
enough if one wants to take action upon a single module change.

Use case :

If an action needs to be taken after all the packages have been
installed or updated : Package <| tag == 'gnocchi-package' |> -> X

Change-Id: I90902e01bd095e1b0f6a2944ceedfc53de6f7b01

TRACE is a logging keyword that is understood by most logging
tools. OpenStack has repurposed this in the past to not be TRACE

commit_message:
Define TRACE logging level

TRACE is a logging keyword that is understood by most logging
tools. OpenStack has repurposed this in the past to not be TRACE
logging but instead be used whenever a Stacktrace was dumped. This
was already fixed in:
I8c618e7b8523bcc0e19a9b77c4d2d5984369a04a

Now in this review, we are adding a new TRACE level set to an
integer halfway between DEBUG and NOTSET which is currently 5.

One can also use LOG.trace for deep tracing of their code as well.
To make it easy for end users to import the TRACE level, added
public constants for all the log levels from logging module. Several
projects import logging just for the constants, this will help
them as well.

Please see the logging guidelines for more info:
https://github.com/openstack/openstack-specs/blob/master/specs/log-guidelines.rst

Change-Id: Ica0e78da5a57c246b3b7499a6ce8c6f410cd6a80

commit_message:
libvirt: move the LibvirtQuobyteVolumeDriver into the quobyte module

The setup in LibvirtVolumeTestCase is moved to a common base test
class so we don't run tests multiple times by extending the
LibvirtVolumeTestCase class in the type-specific volume driver
tests. Helper methods are moved as needed for the tests.

Part of blueprint consolidate-libvirt-fs-volume-drivers

Change-Id: I0a6896e7d1de58b4550f18819113a38799a1fa12

commit_message:
Mock $window for magic-search tests

Provide a mock $window for st-magic-search-spec.js so that it
doesn't modify the URL when running Jasmine in a browser.
Otherwise it adds ?status=shutdown, which if unnoticed and the
jasmine tests re-run, cause other magic search tests to fail.

Change-Id: I8541e54516c0a23c9e5015bc154371e85c3d4367
Fixes-Bug: 1478731

commit_message:
Fix DeprecationWarning when using BaseException.message

Some of the nova unit tests are getting:
"DeprecationWarning: BaseException.message has been deprecated as of Python 2.6 "
when referring to the message attribute of the exception.
Change to use "six.text_type(exception)" to avoid these warning.

Change-Id: I68a62270cac0c2129bc234d420d01ae1096d68d1
Partial-bug: 1479066

commit_message:
Fix description of security group API

If a client doesn't specify the parameter description when calling
the security group API, Nova returns a HTTP400(BadRequest) response
to the client because of
http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/nova/tree/nova/compute/api.py#n3853
So the parameter description of security group API is required now.

Change-Id: I9c9b66f35f267e4b99b8a294ebc23997b25ea920

subject: Correct 'tag' parameter descriptions of Image API
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-07-27 08:13:49.000000000', 'files': ['api-ref/src/wadls/image-api/src/v2/os-image-v2.wadl'], 'message': "Correct 'tag' parameter descriptions of Image API

The Response parameters tables of List images, Get image details,
and Update image of the Image service API v2
contain incorrect description of the 'tag' parameter:

  Parameter  Style  Type        Description
   :
  tag        URI    xsd:string  Image tag.
   :

Because these APIs return the 'tags' parameter
containing an array of image tags,
the description should be the following:

  tags       plain  xsd:dict    Image tags.

To change the description, the '&tagParameter' references
in the response elements of these APIs in os-image-v2.wadl
are changed to '&tagsParameter',
which has already been defined and contains the correct description.

Change-Id: Ibf56dccd4792908a621d307a14513962e82c3a80
Closes-Bug: #1477850
"}]
commit_message:
Correct 'tag' parameter descriptions of Image API

The Response parameters tables of List images, Get image details,
and Update image of the Image service API v2
contain incorrect description of the 'tag' parameter:

  Parameter  Style  Type        Description
   :
  tag        URI    xsd:string  Image tag.
   :

Because these APIs return the 'tags' parameter
containing an array of image tags,
the description should be the following:

  tags       plain  xsd:dict    Image tags.

To change the description, the '&tagParameter' references
in the response elements of these APIs in os-image-v2.wadl
are changed to '&tagsParameter',
which has already been defined and contains the correct description.

Change-Id: Ibf56dccd4792908a621d307a14513962e82c3a80
Closes-Bug: #1477850

commit_message:
Enable hacking/flake8 rules

This commit enables and fixes previously disabled E and F rules:

* E111 indentation is not a multiple of four
* E113 unexpected indentation
* E265 block comment should start with '# '
* H236 Python 3.x incompatible __metaclass__, use six.add_metaclass()
* H238 old style class declaration, use new style (inherit from `object`)
* H405 multi line docstring summary not separated with an empty line
* H701 Empty localization string

Change-Id: Ie0af0d450f81cb5bf274192e6fdce3e41ccb7f88
Closes-Bug: #1478002

commit_message:
Add support for force-delete backups

1. Add _get and _delete method to BackupAdminController.
2. Add force=False arg to delete method in backup api.
3. If force=True, then allow the deletion of backup, which
can be in any state.
4. For chunkeddriver based backup, check the status of backup
from DB in backup loop, if it has changed to deleting, set the
flag is_backup_canceled and clear the data to avoid leaving orphan
object in the object store.
5. Add the flag: support_force_delete=False in BackupDriver. That
indicates if the backup driver supports force deletion.
It should be set to True if the driver that inherits from BackupDriver
supports the force deletion function.
6. If the backup driver doesn't support this feature, and it will return
405 when calling API of force delete.

DocImpact
APIImpact
Add os-force_delete in request body:
*POST /v2/{tenant_id}/backups/{id}/action
{
  "os-force_delete": {}
}
Implements: blueprint support-force-delete-backup

Change-Id: Ia4d36520d2a092730cd1be56e338349e383f9e6b

subject: Remove unnecessary static auth code
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-07-15 00:30:46.000000000', 'files': ['anchor/auth/static.py'], 'message': "Remove unnecessary static auth code

There's no need for special casing initial username and password checks.
Actually it is counterproductive. The checks resulted in different
timings depending on matched username and password length. While very
unlikely in practice, it could be used for discovering extra
information.
There's no performance impact, since passwords will be just a few
characters long.

As a side effect, get 100% test coverage on static auth.

Change-Id: Idc30df4044241b900733ad34c7279a3d0396edcc
"}]
commit_message:
Remove unnecessary static auth code

There's no need for special casing initial username and password checks.
Actually it is counterproductive. The checks resulted in different
timings depending on matched username and password length. While very
unlikely in practice, it could be used for discovering extra
information.
There's no performance impact, since passwords will be just a few
characters long.

commit_message:
Ceph/RBD support

Implements Ceph client configuration. This change adds configuration options
within all of the various OpenStack components to allow them to connect to
and utilize a Ceph rbd backend. A new role was created for ceph_client which
simply implements all of the backend work. This role adds RBD support to
nova, cinder, and glance.

Closes-Bug: #1455238
Change-Id: Ie484ce0bbb93adc53c30be32f291aa5058b20028

Remove ceph_conf from ceph_client/defaults/main.yml

Change-Id: I4cd411d5222b769d6801d5b5a3d1d4e1412eb93f

commit_message:
Activate pep8 check that _ is imported

Remove the specification in tox.ini that _ is a builtin so that
it will no longer assume that _ does not need to be imported.
This helps ensure that the _ from i18n is used.

Activating this check did not flag any violations.

Change-Id: I458c7749de5bd88909f23554485f2adfcb56e2d4

commit_message:
Add timeout value to 'urlaccesscheck check'

This change adds a configurable timeout to 'urlaccesscheck check' to
ensure the script does not hang if there are connectivity issues with
the URL that is being checked.  The default timeout is 60 seconds but
is configurable via a command line option.

This change also adds netifaces to the network_checker requirements.txt
because it was not added as part of
I910c15c2b39a917eb8428bb69271b5dde364b639 so test and installation may
fail on a clean environment.

Change-Id: I363712a6501cc21b89601d5373b5633d5518ca81
Closes-Bug: 1478138
Related-Bug: 1471085
Related-Bug: 1476831
Closed-Bug: 1478622

The first word on the first line of `multipath -l $path` is currently

commit_message:
Multipath device action incorrectly parsed as the device name

The first word on the first line of `multipath -l $path` is currently
being used as the name of a given multipath device. This however can be
an `action:` string when the device is being created, reloaded, resized
etc. In this case the second word is the name of the device.

Change-Id: I8f1f769bb15ec10054e2fd73c4cf621389014cf1
Closes-Bug:1466444

commit_message:
Multipath commands with error messages in stdout fail to parse

This change fixes an issue in find_multipath_device() where the command
output of ‘multipath -l <device>’ would sometimes fail to be parsed if
there were error messages in the stdout string in addition to the
expected output. We will now strip out the error messages before we
attempt to parse the lines.

This change is already present in Cinder [1] and os-brick.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/128755/

Change-Id: I3d48debc7d64f6a891ac37d4c2c5ebddfb5b00b0
Closes-Bug: #1380742

commit_message:
test_zabbix_py system test refactoring

* Using neutron instead of nova
* Segment type choose by env var NEUTRON_SEGMENT_TYPE
  which is 'vlan' by default
* Context manager for SSH sessions
* 'assert_cluster_ready' calls removed, assume network
  verification and ostf will check the same

Change-Id: Ie72ba7c58433f0ebd30d74f55651b940037d92ad
Closes-Bug: #1478922

commit_message:
Remove reference to missing user_group_vars file

The in-tree version of user_group_vars.yml was removed in
30f9443c5d2f3a3bbb51bf75ad5743ef46c9b0ef, but the corresponding
reference in the upgrade script was not also updated.

This commit changes the behavior to remove the file from /etc/ if found.

Change-Id: I9f5b061289c5f43e32983845469f5123cc9f209d
Closes-Bug: #1479501
(cherry picked from commit 928af8a9ac4e031f8387dd0445223fb3a7c48ed1)

commit_message:
Change DB 'get_category' request

Previously if user provide a unicode named category through
muranoclient murano fails as far as it can't work with the names
at all and unicode names in particular. Now this issue is fixed
and we can filter through category.name not only category.id

Change-Id: I7aaddd1a9da53e3b94aa1e33a71fb33a33fb4f59
Depends-On: I31974dc6044ffcd7411e0a5ed95b2599587004fa

commit_message:
libvirt: move volume/remotefs/quobyte modules under volume subdir

As part of the refactor for the libvirt volume drivers, move the
volume-specific modules under a new 'volume' subdirectory.

The next step will be breaking the volume drivers out into their
own specific modules.

Part of blueprint consolidate-libvirt-fs-volume-drivers

Change-Id: I5fc2425d2c25076ea87686b2e41be35f66ebb923

commit_message:
Fix error message appearance in case there are no apps avaliable

There are two cases that handled in this commit:
1) If no packages in the catalog - corresponding message appears.
   Link to the openstack catalog is provided.

2) Now message appears if there are no apps while specifying a category
   or while searching

Now no 'Application components' row appeared together with it's controls
(such as serach and category selector) if there are no apps in the catalog

Change-Id: I240c70a77fea7e52d13bac8ff0f15218d3561a49
Closes-Bug: #1477107

commit_message:
Make ntpd listen all interfaces

* Remove ntpd listen restrictions
* Remove client run on controllers
* Add ubuntu service overrides for ntp
* ntp server should use only ipv4
* update dnsmasq to only listen on management vrouter vip

TestImpact
Change-Id: Ic78394fddaafa82e085c55a1a0fdd3c46d4f0089
Closes-Bug: 1466090

commit_message:
Handle non-numeric files in key_repository

It is very likely administrators will leave behind bits and pieces in a
live environment. One cannot assume that all of the files in a directory
will be the ones created by Keystone.

Change-Id: I5841a11f599f79d2efbe1a176f499e280a91cb37
Closes-Bug: #1478656

commit_message:
MongoDB user management - root enable/show

Enable the root-enable/show functionality for the MongoDB guestagent.

- Enable the codepaths in the MongoDB guestagent manager.
- Use PyMongo to make the required calls to MongoDB in the service.

RELATED CHANGES:

--\ authentication
   --\ users create/list/show/delete
      --- users root enable/show
      --- users access grant/show/revoke
   --- database

Partially Implements: blueprint mongodb-users
Change-Id: I94f1e5d262f5a340e84fa2db9fbf9e251acf940d

commit_message:
Add stderr to log in check_repo_managment

With output suppression in check_repo_managment there is impossible
to know why exactly 'yum update' or 'apt-get update' failed. Adding
stderr to error message, suppressing stdout at the same time to
reduce log size.

Change-Id: I948a580ed283d9c1a271b8126a248e3d4bba9bb3
Closes-Bug: #1456178

[{'number': 18, 'created': '2015-07-14 01:06:22.000000000', 'files': ['spec/acceptance/keystone_wsgi_apache_spec.rb'], 'message': 'acceptance: run keystone in a WSGI server

Running keystone via eventlet is deprecated as of Kilo in favor of
running in a WSGI server (e.g. mod_wsgi).

commit_message:
acceptance: run keystone in a WSGI server

Running keystone via eventlet is deprecated as of Kilo in favor of
running in a WSGI server (e.g. mod_wsgi).
Support for keystone under eventlet will be removed in the "M"-Release.

This patch test an upgrade between eventlet to wsgi.
In the future, the eventlet test will be dropped in favor of wsgi which
will be default.

commit_message:
remove conntrackd package

As per bug discussion, conntrackd is actually not needed for netfilter
framework, and given that users do not appear to find the logs useful
(the only reason we're using conntrackd), let's just remove it.

This commit also defines a variable container_remove_packages so that
the list of packages to remove from containers can be added to in the
future.

NOTE: removing conntrackd does not unload the kernel conntrack modules
or disable the netfilter conntrack framework. It simply means we are not
gathering ostensibly useless logging. The kernel conntrack flows can
still be interrogated with the 'conntrack' userspace cli tool, for real
time debugging.

Change-Id: Ic74e65a6fe27060dc94bfc2f250cd53fb153c7c8
Closes-Bug: 1457196

When pooling an Ironic node to check it's states we were getting the whole
node object representation. That is heavy weight because it includes
everything from that node, including sometimes the whole configdrive
(a base64 string of it). We don't need to do it, the Ironic API exposes
an endpoint (v1/nodes/<uuid>/states) that will return only the current
states of a specific node. This patch is updating the code to use that
endpoint and stop wasting bandwidth with information we don't care about
when checking for the node states.

Change-Id: I163f9b99a89218c794410c0cf69c214c951bc61b
"}]
commit_message:
Ironic: Lightweight node states check

When pooling an Ironic node to check it's states we were getting the whole
node object representation. That is heavy weight because it includes
everything from that node, including sometimes the whole configdrive
(a base64 string of it). We don't need to do it, the Ironic API exposes
an endpoint (v1/nodes/<uuid>/states) that will return only the current
states of a specific node. This patch is updating the code to use that
endpoint and stop wasting bandwidth with information we don't care about
when checking for the node states.

Change-Id: I163f9b99a89218c794410c0cf69c214c951bc61b

commit_message:
Fix catalog compilation when not configuring endpoint

Previously when you set $configure_endpoint to false and did not have a
keystone_endpoint resource with the same name as is defined by
neutron::keystone::auth, the catalog would not be compiled. This was
because a relationship was being established where one resource in the
relationship didn't exist. This changes this so that the relationship
involving the Keystone endpoint is only defined if $configure_endpoint
is set to true.

Change-Id: I1ee51f33ffd1bf20578cd56120ee5be8e6fa0133
Co-Authored-By: Risto Laurikainen <risto.laurikainen@csc.fi>
Co-Authored-By: Gael Chamoulaud <gchamoul@redhat.com>
Closes-Bug: 1368686

commit_message:
Create packages for quota modules

This patch simply renames quota modules introducing two
new packages:
1) neutron.quota
2) neutron.db.quota

This paves the way for adding more quota related modules.
Unit tests paths are changed accordingly, as well as references
to moved modules.
This patch hovewer preserves the ability of importing
neutron.db.quota_db in order to avoid breaking repositories which
use neutron as a requirement.

Change-Id: I946e87f1b2ebb3e80d64aecfe58aeff9f81896f3
Related-blueprint: better-quotas

revisions:

POC for hooks functionality that allows us to do following:
- perform some operations before driver method calls
- perform some operations after driver method calls
- suppress errors raised within hooks
- change results returned to manager
- use results from 'pre_hook' and driver's method in 'post_hook'

commit_message:
[POC] Add hooks for share driver operations

POC for hooks functionality that allows us to do following:
- perform some operations before driver method calls
- perform some operations after driver method calls
- suppress errors raised within hooks
- change results returned to manager
- use results from 'pre_hook' and driver's method in 'post_hook'
- no dependency on drivers
- have instances of manager and driver

Use cases:
- common notification
- performng of specific operations like replication, update of policies, etc...

Change-Id: I732cbaffcb136f22d13f2782f56f62023c1bee30

commit_message:
Add DictOfListOfStrings type of field

For Scheduler hints, sometimes some hints can be either strings or list of strings.
In that case, we prefer to accept all of them as list of strings and provide a way
to provide a DictOfListOfStrings type of field for the future scheduler_hints field
of the RequestSpec object.

NOTE: this type is also proposed in o.vo by https://review.openstack.org/205110

Partially-Implements: blueprint request-spec-object

Change-Id: Ibf6e9b83dcd676bab076821f8eca335974d49f06

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-07-24 12:32:08.000000000', 'files': ['fuelweb_test/testrail/report.py'], 'message': "Add a key to process a single job from Jenkins view for TestRail

- add the key '--one-job', '-o ' to spesify a name of a single job

commit_message:
Add a key to process a single job from Jenkins view for TestRail

- add the key '--one-job', '-o ' to spesify a name of a single job
  that should be reported to TestRail instead of whole swarm jobs;
- add the key '--statistics', '-s' (bool), that enable making a
  statistics for bugs that were linked to the test cases for
  Jenkins jobs in specified job runner or view;
- fix error when 'Bug with id NNN is private or doesn't exist.',
  just skip bugs with such IDs to avoid error:
  'local variable 'bug' referenced before assignment'

Change-Id: I26fad28f14e43d07e115fa1a5fee8b56f5227f23
Closes-Bug:#1477972

The in-tree version of user_group_vars.yml was removed in
30f9443c5d2f3a3bbb51bf75ad5743ef46c9b0ef, but the corresponding
reference in the upgrade script was not also updated.

This commit changes the behavior to remove the file from /etc/ if found.

Instead of allowing executor types to be provided for
now just allow only strings to be provided, and restrict
that set of strings to known working executors that will
not have thread locking issues (until we have a way to use
compatible thread locks that match the executor we should
likely not allow to many types to be passed in).

This will likely get better when the following merges:

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/203885/

Change-Id: I2b5c2bdc00e59aca8ba150ef57a4b72c8c671227
'}]
commit_message:
Be more restrictive on the executors users can provide

Instead of allowing executor types to be provided for
now just allow only strings to be provided, and restrict
that set of strings to known working executors that will
not have thread locking issues (until we have a way to use
compatible thread locks that match the executor we should
likely not allow to many types to be passed in).

This will likely get better when the following merges:

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/203885/

Change-Id: I2b5c2bdc00e59aca8ba150ef57a4b72c8c671227

commit_message:
update teardown.sh to remove mongodb

If mongodb has been installed as a backend for ceilometer (as it is by
the bootstrap-aio script), we want it removed in the teardown.  This
commit updates the teardown.sh to do just that.

Also s/remote_pip_pacakges/remove_pip_packages/

Change-Id: I909feac8321feaf66f44642cac1b729ded10d2fb

commit_message:
VMware: Fix protocol in backend stats

The VMDK driver reports the protocol as 'LSI Logic SCSI' in
backend stats. This patch changes the protocol to 'vmdk'
which is in sync with driver support matrix at:
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/CinderSupportMatrix

Change-Id: I182929d8d386d2f6466d326971da510b6898133f

commit_message:
Keystone Federation Identity Provider Configuration

This change adds the bits necessary to configure Keystone as an
identity provider (IdP) for an external service provider (SP).

* New variables to configure Keystone as an identity provider are now
  supported under a root `keystone_idp` variable. Example configurations
  can be seen in Keystone's defaults file. This configuration includes
  the location of the signing certificate, authentication endpoints and
  list of allowed service providers.

* xmlsec1 is installed in the Keystone containers when IdP configuration
  is enabled.

* The IdP metadata and signing certiciate are generated and installed.

Implements: blueprint keystone-federation
Change-Id: I81455e593e3059633a55f7e341511d5ad9eba76f

commit_message:
Alter unit test to match bug and cleanup ext logic

The unit test for bug #1443342 was only testing that a side effect
leading to the bug didn't occur (comparing object identities). This
patch updates the unit test to fully assert that the bug itself
doesn't occur without checking implementation details.

This also eliminates the branching that led to the original issue by
using setdefault to always return a dict to update.

Related-Bug: #1443342
Change-Id: I6c48681aa49c17bbadffa12bad1eea272c483437

commit_message:
Do not use VolumeTasks in AWS Instance create

Use volume progress objects instead (as in volume attachment resources).

Module volume_tasks and class scheduler.PollingTaskGroup have been removed,
as they are no longer used anywhere.

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-07-17 07:18:40.000000000', 'files': ['requirements.txt', 'setup.py', 'tox.ini'], 'message': 'Sync with global requirements

Update to get the same versions in that are used elsewhere.

Version change for: pbr, testtools
Updated ../docs-specs/requirements.txt:
    pbr>=0.6,!=0.7,<1.0            ->   pbr>=1.3,<2.0
    testtools>=0.9.36,!=1.2.0      ->   testtools>=1.4.0

Also, stop specifying requirements.txt in tox.ini.

As PBR already injects the contents of requirements.txt into

Change-Id: Id4ed6e53bcf199e78a02a5f5d079e2ca45642af4
'}]
commit_message:
Sync with global requirements

Update to get the same versions in that are used elsewhere.

Version change for: pbr, testtools
Updated ../docs-specs/requirements.txt:
    pbr>=0.6,!=0.7,<1.0            ->   pbr>=1.3,<2.0
    testtools>=0.9.36,!=1.2.0      ->   testtools>=1.4.0

Also, stop specifying requirements.txt in tox.ini.

As PBR already injects the contents of requirements.txt into
setup_requires, there is no need for tox to explicitly install them.
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-July/069663.html

Change-Id: Id4ed6e53bcf199e78a02a5f5d079e2ca45642af4

commit_message:
Add a new DictOfListOfStrings type of field

In order to coerce correctly some fields that are primarly dictionaries having
either strings or list of strings as values, we need to provide a new field type
which would accept only list of strings as values for dicts so anyone who would
want to use that type would just have to make sure to hydrate all the items by
putting them into a single list.

Change-Id: I708860357e17bcc70733187c3289dd859b09c60b

commit_message:
Set default inventory file for inventory-manage.py

The script inventory-manage.py takes a file argument. The default name
for this file, in the project, is rpc_inventory.json. Not only is
it the default but the rest of the project assumes that it will be that
name.

This commit sets the default argument for the file parameter to this
assumed file name - 'rpc_inventory.json'.

Change-Id: I635122d22bb0467aad21f48dccda1bc0444518c1
Closes-bug: #1454324
(manual backport from commit 576831481262b93dfdf72f078a4b620a7ac130fb)

commit_message:
Necessary extending of objects to perform upgrade

The upgrade procedure should create a new cluster with the same
parameters as the original cluster. The new method was intoduced to
parameters the cluster that was created with. The return value of the
new method is compatible with the data that are expected by the create
method.

A set of hooks of the extension mechanism was extended by the
fire_callback_on_cluster_delete hook. This hooks is fired when cluster
is deleted.

Two opposite method were added: get_assigned_vips and
assign_given_vips_for_net_groups. The first method returns all assigned
VIPs of the cluster and the second complementary method receives the
same format that the first returns to assign given VIPs.

The patch has some impact on the get_admin_network_group method. This
impact consist of adding a new filter called node_group_id that allows
to filter network groups by ID of the node group when there are no any
nodes in the cluster.

Implements blueprint: nailgun-api-env-upgrade-extensions

Change-Id: I156d3c71a7e832a2eb99a1058a6ac628fab71483

commit_message:
set correct swift dispersion tenant

In kilo, the swift dispersion user is created as a member of
the 'service' tenant.  However, we are populating the
swift-dispersion.conf as though it was a member of the admin tenant (as
it was in juno).  This commit fixes that, and makes
swift-dispersion-report (and any monitoring plugins that rely on it)
work again

Change-Id: I0e9b9ccaa487ee0242346ee279821aa09dd5b022
Closes-Bug: #1479006
(cherry picked from commit 23e796c344ba87f0ac6bee436a9b3d3ad4bfb269)

commit_message:
Listen on :: instead of 0.0.0.0 by default

If Manila API runs on a system with IPv6, it listens on IPv4 by default,
but clients try IPv6 first. The resulting retry is unnecessary. On Linux,
it is easy to listen on both address families simply by opening an IPv6
listening socket, so this patch makes use of that feature.

The listening address may be set explicitly as before. Only the default
is changed by this patch.

Closes-Bug: #1338825

commit_message:
tasks.yaml, network_roles.yaml are optional files for V3

For V3:
 - tasks.yaml and network_roles.yaml are not mandatory,
 - validation is skipped if optional file is not exists,
 - unit test class TestValidatorV3 added,
 - tests for validators V1, V2 extracted to separate files.

Added error messages for empty and not exist files.
Fixed error for task without parameters for V1, V2.

Change-Id: I3eaf12a7a22a35067bae04b6bb5cc81a6835cfd5
Closes-Bug: #1477128

commit_message:
Fix failure to create glance https connection pool

Due to a typo in an attribute named, an Attribute error is raised
causing failure in connection to glance through HTTPS

Urllib3 PoolManager class has a connection_pool_kw attribute
but not connection_kw

Closes-Bug: #1479020
Change-Id: Id4d6a5bdcf971d09e80043fd2ab399e208fd931c

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-07-25 13:53:36.000000000', 'files': ['api-ref/src/wadls/netconn-api/src/common.ent'], 'message': 'Fix style of tenant_id to query (List ports)

"Style" of "tenant_id" in "Request parameters" of "List

commit_message:
Fix style of tenant_id to query (List ports)

"Style" of "tenant_id" in "Request parameters" of "List
ports" is "plain", but it should be "query".

In api-site/api-ref/src/wadls/netconn-api/src/common.ent,
"!ENTITY portListQueryParameters" uses &tenantIdOwnerNetwork;
to represent "tenant_id (Optional)", but it's only valid
for "tenant_id (Optional)" with *plain* style.

Change-Id: I1899be7e9375d4e14bc4923e80c9f96cff99794d
Closes-Bug: #1477988

missing "Error response codes".

The methods should have the following error response codes.

  - List networks
    Unauthorized(401)

  - Create network
    Bad request(400), Unauthorized(401)

  - Show network details
    Unauthorized(401), Not found(404)

  - Update network
    Bad request(400), Unauthorized(401), Not found(404)

  - Delete network
    Unauthorized(401), Not found(404), Conflict(409)

Actually, "Delete network" is missing "Normal response codes" as
well, and that should be '204'. That can be fixed in this patch.

Change-Id: I3246f85fccd3b4980410954643a133583d3ab939
Closes-Bug: #1477527

commit_message:
Fix Orchestration request parameters of stack_update API

1) "environment", "timeout_mins" are changed to "Optional" from 
   "Required".
2) "param_name-n", "param_value-n" are deleted because these 
   parameters are combined into 'parameters'.

Closes-bug: #1475311

commit_message:
Set secret key for metadata access via md proxy

Between nova-api and neutron-metadata-agent, there
is a mechanism to encrypt the data with
shared secret. This patch sets a secret
in nova.conf and metadata_agent.ini in order to
excercise the code path for the encryption.

Change-Id: Ie98502e0747670eec468aad75b47d52961e674a6

Now that this gate job is reasonably stable, hardly a test or two
failing, it would be good to get some more test results and log files
to help debug the last few bugs that remain. So, make it run on the
check gate but keep it non-voting still.

commit_message:
Install proper mysql-client package

We should not install default mysql-client package, that is
defined in mysql::params::client_package_name. But instead we need
to calculate proper version of mysql-client in exactly the same
way as we do it in database.pp task when evaluate mysql::server
class. To do so we introduce new class galera::client and declare
it instead of ::mysql.

Change-Id: Ib118450656f99f68358e84a61b1684b8025e483c
Closes-bug: #1476599

commit_message:
nailgun::cobbler: Ubuntu and CentOS based bootstrap can coexist

Add a new attribute called `bootstrap_flavor' so Ubuntu based bootstrap
image can coexist with that based on CentOS. Use the CentOS based
bootstrap as the default for now.

Closes-Bug: #1478441
Change-Id: I34ff183a9b0cdc53fa17034254d8618ffa388208

Old ocf file cleanup

This change removes missed ocf scripts from deployment/ and moves
any still referenced files to files/fuel-ha-utils. Also cleans up
commented out ocf files from the puppet code.

Related-Bug: 1457441

commit_message:
Add access-level support in VNX Manila driver

Manila framework adds a new blueprint to set access-level for a share so
that admin can grant read-only/read-write permission to specific share.
This fix is to implement access-level both for CIFS and NFS share
in VNX Manila driver.

Change-Id: Ib651300978c451ca9b0d4b768c1f06d44d51a951
Implements: bp emc-vnx-manila-driver-read-only-share

commit_message:
set/unset volume image metadata

This patch implements:
- Create, delete, update APIs for modifying volume image metadata.
- Refactoring in the volume API to accommodate both user and
  image metadata.
- All of the necessary testcases needed for the changes.

DocImpact
APIImpact
Partially implements: bp support-modify-volume-image-metadata

subject: Aodh: add Heat functional tests
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-07-20 09:52:02.000000000', 'files': ['jenkins/jobs/aodh.yaml', 'zuul/layout.yaml'], 'message': 'Aodh: add Heat functional tests

Heat have a functional tests suite to test autoscaling with ceilometer.
Ceilometer have recently move the alarming code to a new repository,
the alarming is now provided by aodh-* service.

This job will test the heat functional tests suite against
aodh-api instead of the old ceilometer-api.

This will ensures that migration to the new service works and will
not break the heat gate in the future when we really switch to aodh.

Change-Id: I1b13c375a0820612b9db0a33358ef41dda155fa2
'}]
commit_message:
Aodh: add Heat functional tests

Heat have a functional tests suite to test autoscaling with ceilometer.
Ceilometer have recently move the alarming code to a new repository,
the alarming is now provided by aodh-* service.

This job will test the heat functional tests suite against
aodh-api instead of the old ceilometer-api.

This will ensures that migration to the new service works and will
not break the heat gate in the future when we really switch to aodh.

Change-Id: I1b13c375a0820612b9db0a33358ef41dda155fa2

commit_message:
Fix alembic migration script for vpnaas

Alembic migration script 56893333aa52_fix_identifier_map_fk.py
tries to change the 'ipsec_site_conn_id' column without disabling
the 'cisco_csr_identifier_map_ibfk_1' constraint. Also, there is
no need to resize existing data with a existing fk constraint,
which would already limit it to VARCHAR(36).

Change-Id: Ie820e94b43b572ec201b4c6174a93682a6cd47ab
Closes-Bug: #1464825

commit_message:
Remove deprecated config options for Liberty

num_iscsi_scan_tries and backup_service have been deprecated for at
least two releases or longer.

Change-Id: I4c99e0aa06fd6ff8fc38dda29e8132e0edd69257
UpgradeImpact: removed num_iscsi_scan_tries and backup_service conf opts

commit_message:
Correct fcntl.flock use in Pidfile.unlock

This change corrects Pidfile.unlock[1] implementation, indeed currently
it uses fcntl.flock response as a condition but fcntl.flock is a "void"
function.

[1] neutron.agent.linux.daemon

Closes-Bug: #1472725
Change-Id: If2320f29095ed388f9f6fe59d4d9b80d04adaa85

commit_message:
Windows iSCSI: Add CHAP authentication support

This patch adds CHAP authentication support for the Windows iSCSI
driver.

One-way CHAP authentication is used, having the CHAP credentials
generated when the iSCSI target is created.

Implements: blueprint windows-iscsi-chap

commit_message:
Add Gunicorn

This patch adds Gunicorn to the global dependencies. It's used in Kuryr
to serve a libnetwork remote driver through a Unix domain socket [1].
Originally uWSGI was a candidate but it's released under GPLv2 and
Gunicorn's license is MIT License.

Check list for new requirements:

* Is the library actively maintained?

  Yes. The last commit was made 10 days ago and it's been released
  frequently since 2010 [2].

* Is the library good code?

  Yes. It was downloaded 304,698 times in the last month [3].

* Is the library python 3 compatible?

  Yes. Python 3.x >= 3.2 is required.

* Is the library license compatible?

  Yes. It's released under MIT License.

* Is the library already packaged in the distros we target (Ubuntu
  latest / Fedora latest)?

  Ubuntu 14.04LTS trusy has a package which version is 17.5 [4] and RHEL6
  does 18.0 [5].

* Is the function of this library already covered by other libraries in
  global-requirements.txt?

  I don't think so.

[1]: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/204820/
[2]: http://docs.gunicorn.org/en/latest/news.html
[3]: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/gunicorn/
[4]: http://packages.ubuntu.com/trusty/gunicorn
[5]: http://rpms.famillecollet.com/rpmphp/zoom.php?rpm=python-gunicorn

Change-Id: I175893fbffaba6be2089df15b25b7bd31d5d0213
Signed-off-by: Taku Fukushima <tfukushima@midokura.com>

commit_message:
Re-enable building of heat_repo_plugins

The building of heat_repo_plugins was disabled while upstream heat
sorted out issues w/ the contrib packages and pbr >= 0.11.0.  The
upstream fix has since gone in (see
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/179671/) so we can now continue to
build heat_repo_plugins as we were prior to pbr 0.11.0 dropping.

NOTE: heat SHA has been bumped to include the commit in review 179671.

Closes-Bug: #1453864
Change-Id: Ibeffd38fc3229ab4effc95ef256ce8af3a6ffc9f
(cherry picked from commit ed491df7ee948831c17b34a90085dd7976300499)

commit_message:
Revert "Add temporary non voting multinode smoke jobs"

These jobs have run successfully for a few days (once you factor out the
failures related to  Ia9155bc565ad79af44d88acc06759be2bf4e5f20.

Now that we know tempest-smoke should pass in multinode, these jobs have
served their purpose. Teaching grenade how to do multinode should just
work w.r.t. to tempest-smoke (there are no 'openstack' bugs that we need
to fix first).

This reverts commit fc12a7d5e2eef0c52cf8de9b1b02b522baf310ef.

Change-Id: I895fa4574cde062a818574e9686a579a5034a19e

commit_message:
Decouple the queue and subscription

Now some parts of the subscription storage drivers is assuming
the queue_controller is in the same storage. But unfortunately,
it's not always true. This patch fixes it, but there is no new
test case involved.

Closes-Bug: #1471193

commit_message:
Try luksFormat up to 3 times in case the device is in use

Cinder change I03f8cae05cc117e14f7482115de685fc9f3fa54a is failing for
some volume driver third party CI like NetApp iSCSI because the device
is in use when formatting the device for LUKS.

This change adds a retry counter to the luksFormat command execution
like we did in commit eef97cdf4bb7f426d7feb394ef54510db8b1656b for
closing the volume and hitting intermittent in-use issues.

Closes-Bug: #1470562
Related-Bug: #1440227

Change-Id: I0cb32a6f9fbe68ae033ad00534512aa5d82a417b

commit_message:
Enable python34 tests for nova/tests/unit/scheduler/test*.py

nova/pci/stats.py:
  need to specify a key parameter which is a function that returns
  a sorting key. since the original intention with pool_cmp was to
  sort by number of items in each pool, we just use key parameter
  with a lambda
nova/scheduler/filters/trusted_filter.py
nova/scheduler/host_manager.py
  needed list() so we could delete stuff inside the loop in py3
nova/tests/unit/scheduler/test_filter_scheduler.py
  needed the import of test as some tests were failing in py3,
  added noqa as test is not explicitly referenced within the
  module
nova/tests/unit/scheduler/test_scheduler_options.py
  need BytesIO for py3, StringIO will fail in many tests
nova/tests/unit/scheduler/test_scheduler_utils.py
  message is not available in py3, so we need to adjust
  use test.nested already added in a previous commit
nova/test.py
  if we have a key which is a list, treat it just like a set
nova/utils.py
  use reduce from six and explicitly typcast version_int as
  an integer

Change-Id: Ic862873f38767f12b990a030b5812ae50a44c4d0

commit_message:
libvirt: update docstring in blockinfo module for disk_info

The docstring was listing disk_info as a tuple but it's a dict in the
code and it wasn't pointing out that boot_index is an optional field.

Long-term we should probably convert disk_info into an object (doesn't
need to be versioned, but would be cleaner as an object). I started
doing this with a namedtuple but the format and boot_index fields being
optional makes namedtuple a bit messy.

Change-Id: I6721cad9245e8722481c4c63023bb8b7193317ac

commit_message:
libvirt: handle rescue flag first in blockinfo.get_disk_mapping

If rescue is True, we don't need to get the flavor object from the
instance (which could lazy load it from the database) or figure out the
pre-assigned device names for the block_device_info list.

This just re-arranges the order of calls to be more efficient.

The related unit test is updated to show that get_disk_mapping works if
rescue=True and there is no Flavor object in the instance passed in.

Change-Id: I5ac7e4d3129c67db4efde0dda71c41b747952263

commit_message:
tweak graphviz formatting for readability

The "group" tag on nodes can be used to create vertical alignment, all
nodes in a group which are connected will end up in one column. This
makes reading the flow chart a bit easier.

Add a " " before the "no" edges otherwise they are left justified
completely to the vertical edge, and make it kind of gorpy to read.

Change-Id: Ife11e905ea6fdd97e1459fbbc001324eb946f9e4

commit_message:
Add security_group creation test without desc

If Neutron is used as a backend, security_group creation fails by not
passing description parameter. That is an internal error, and that
should be fixed later.
This patch is for reproducing the problem on the gate and sharing the
problem. After fixing, this test will be helpful for blocking the same
problem happens.

Change-Id: I880f1f56dc3e4293f6a278e344aa01b3c21314e2
Related-Bug: #1460875

commit_message:
Dell SC: Add support for ManageableVD

Added support for the ManageableVD volume driver class. This also
meant the driver changed from inheriting the volumedriver class to
inheriting the assorted *VD classes.

A few things about our ManageableVD support. We only allow management
of a volume if it is sized in multiples of 1GB. We only allow
management of volumes that are not currently mapped to a server on the
Storage Center. id-types of source-id (DeviceId on the Storage Center)
and source-name (Volume Name on the Storage Center) are supported.

Change-Id: Iecc93ce1654111e1292cfc1931d1eda4abd08595

commit_message:
Corrected the "nova-quota-class" example in Operations Guide

I updated the "nova quota-class update" example in the "Managing Projects and
Users" chapter which incorrectly uses "instances" instead of "--instances".
The new example is "nova quota-class-update default --instances 15"

Closes-Bug: #1479328

commit_message:
virt: convert hardware module to use nova.objects.ImageMeta

Convert the APIs in the nova.virt.hardware module to expect to
receive an instance of nova.objects.ImageMeta instead of a
dict.

Update the virt drivers to convert the dict into an ImageMeta
module, as a stepping stone, until they to are converted to
use ImageMeta throughout.

Change-Id: Iac034d864cd0265759aaa7c8049fafa276763cc0

commit_message:
Add update tests for policies and rules

This patch adds tests for 'update' for both policies and rules. This
completes the CRUD tests and leaves the association/disassociation for
a later patch. Note that deleting a rule isn't tested explicitly
because of a bug with the rule delete logic on the server side. Once
that code is fixed, the test should be added.

to_dict() for policies should also convert any rules inside rule lists
to dicts too, otherwise API layer receives rule object __repr__ strings
instead of actual dicts. This patch introduces a fix to the existing
to_dict() code to properly support policies.

This patch also modifies the base infra to create policies and rules for
admins and not for tenant.

Partially-Implements: blueprint quantum-qos-api
Change-Id: I13870680d7756be9dd020135bc8e91d1c12f728d
Co-Authored-By: Ihar Hrachyshka <ihrachys@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Glance index visibility should only be for v1

The fix for bug 1478294 caused a regression in indexing, because the image
object coming in does not have a pop function on it, causing images to not
be indexed at all.

This changes this to only do visibility "fixing" on notifications.

Change-Id: I62e6df2458d802aa8c776e8c87fe49a01e4b71f3
Closes-Bug: #1479150
Co-Authored-By: Lakshmi N Sampath <lakshmi.sampath@hp.com>

commit_message:
Add HTTP Async Batch call

In order to make multiple async calls in javascript, we need to nest them.
This makes the code unreadable at some point. There is a better way to
batch multiple async calls using defer and promises. This patch provides a
way to batch async calls and handle it once ALL async calls are complete.

Change-Id: I28beb4fd8efdd5ea85cadd639d6f9daf78de07a4
Closes-Bug: #1479162

commit_message:
Adding wizard modal service

The way angular-bootstrap modal work is a bit strange.
This is a problem because it requires us to define controller A for open.
And it also forces controller B to define close and dismiss.
The result is a bunch of controllers just to open a modal dialog.

This service aims to simplify that by centralizing open, close, and dismiss.
It also provides some default options that you must override via init.

Link to documentation:
https://angular-ui.github.io/bootstrap/#/modal

commit_message:
Adding methods to network driver to get more info

The network driver needs the ability to retrieve specific information about
subnets and ports and pass that information to other components.  Having info
about the subnet gives us cidr and gateway data that is valuable when setting
up the amphora's routes for the separation of tenant data and management data.
Because of this need, methods to retrieve network, subnet, and port details
has been added.

This also adds a another data model AmphoraNetworkConfig that contains subnet
and port information for the vip, vrrp, and ha networks on an amphora.  A
network task has been added that builds this data structure by calling the new
methods added to the network driver.

Change-Id: Ica912337c7d52659a9733096878664f734f27b00

commit_message:
Adopt openstack-config for eslint

Since openstack-config for eslint is now published on npm we should use
it as basis for our linting rules. It is actually stricter, than our
current semi-default config as it enables some of the previously
unchecked rules.

Partially implements: blueprint add-js-lint-jobs

Change-Id: I0cb8247167a44f30a657693442f99a87f116350a

lbaas namespace so that load balancers can reach

commit_message:
Ensure database options registered for tests

DeprecatedTestCase and DeprecatedOverrideTestCase use options in the
database section, but these options won't be registered unless
keystone.common.sql.initialize() is called.

This caused the python34 tests to fail with

 oslo_config.cfg.NoSuchOptError: no such option: database

bp python3

Closes-Bug: 1474491
Change-Id: Ic6376142e5e14f1b25cc203c5b37751dc0a25981

commit_message:

handier to explain when that happens via a symbolic name in the
filename. Add a --name option to worlddump to allow it.

commit_message:
Define IptablesNatDriver stateful nat driver

This change defines IptablesNatDriver: driver to manage iptables-based
(stateful) nat and removes current implementation from router_info
module[1].

This change is an enabler to stateless/stateful nats, follow-up changes
will define tc-based (stateless) nat and allow to choose what
implementation to use.

[1] neutron.agent.l3.router_info

Partially-Implements: blueprint stateless-floatingips
Change-Id: Ie1f00d7ead08bb33e76e7f4403a1c30cd72fb664

commit_message:
Check router is def gw before adding floating IP

If there are multiple routers that have ports on the appropriate private
net and are gateways, the first one found will be selected for a
floating-ip allocation.  Sometimes, that's not the router that is the
default gateway for instances, this change puts an additional check in
place.

Change-Id: Iaeedeb4e76e03801ad0f810d55bcfd2be174a381
Closes-Bug: 1458471

commit_message:
Support port metering

Though now we have metering agent based on metering label, but
there are still some scenarios it can't meet.  Such as for the
VMs directly plugged on provider network or when the traffic
doesn't go through a virtual router. This patch will add the
support for port metering to cover those cases.

blueprint port-metering

Co-Authored-By: Sylvain Afchain(sylvain.afchain@enovance.com)

Change-Id: I20658a07753ea5efa4e95cf2fa3ac7a0eb3818c5

commit_message:
Vmware NSXv: Allow admin to control security-groups rule logging

NSXv distributed firewall expose api to control rule logging,
as for the moment, admin user can use this feature only from inside of
the distributed firewall.
This patch make use of this api to provide the cloud admin with three ways
to control security-group logging:

    - log whenever security-group rule is matched
    - log when a packet doesn't match any security-group rule
    - log whenever security-group rule is matched for selected
      security-groups

Closes-Bug: #1449901
Change-Id: Id9b8376e3a30201434679a75613fb95aabf09b34

commit_message:
Add additional time for starting l3 agents during scheduling

If l3 agent get killed and there are a lot of resources assigned
on it, the agent on which this resources are rescheduling can be
marked as dead for neutron-server because state reports are not
received in agent_down_time*2.

This is similar issue which was previously found for DHCP agent.

Co-Authored-By: Eugene Nikanorov <enikanorov@mirantis.com>

Closes-bug: #1440761

Change-Id: Id00cbeafe0d830ee9386fee253fc49b96e6a7611

commit_message:
Use stevedore to load nat driver

This change defines the "nat_driver" option used to load (using
stevedore) nat driver implementation. One driver implementation is
available: the "stateful" driver, the current implementation.

This change is an enabler to stateless/stateful nats, follow-up
changes will define tc-based (stateless) nat driver.

Partially-Implements: blueprint stateless-floatingips

Change-Id: I005ba893ef556f98619045c6f36dc7284b5df125

commit_message:
Handle KeyError for local_vlan_map in port_bound

OVS-agent's network_delete calls reclaim_local_vlan, which removes
the corresponding entry from local_vlan_map. If it happens at a wrong
moment, main thread can end up with raising KeyError in port_bound.

Change-Id: I411c92386e48dbd6435d5daa4217e386ce463ed0
Closes-Bug: #1455338

Description:
When openvswitch restarts, neutron_ovs_agent will reset the br-tun bridge,
which removes all tunnel ports/flows.

Each neutron_ovs_agent could maintain all l2 population fdb entries locally and
make every fdb add/remove/update operations thread-safe to improve the
reliability.

Implementation:
If l2 population is enabled, it maintains all l2 population fdb entries locally
and recreates ports/flows.

Closes-Bug: #1332450

Co-Authored-By: Romil Gupta <romilg@hp.com>
Co-Authored-By: Neethi Shashidhar <neethi209@gmail.com>

Change-Id: Ie7dc547e41ac33b2ba830a0c3a3524f2bf67fcb8
'}]
commit_message:
br-tun lost ports/flows if openvswitch restart

Description:
When openvswitch restarts, neutron_ovs_agent will reset the br-tun bridge,
which removes all tunnel ports/flows.

Each neutron_ovs_agent could maintain all l2 population fdb entries locally and
make every fdb add/remove/update operations thread-safe to improve the
reliability.

Implementation:
If l2 population is enabled, it maintains all l2 population fdb entries locally
and recreates ports/flows.

Closes-Bug: #1332450

Co-Authored-By: Romil Gupta <romilg@hp.com>
Co-Authored-By: Neethi Shashidhar <neethi209@gmail.com>

Change-Id: Ie7dc547e41ac33b2ba830a0c3a3524f2bf67fcb8

commit_message:
Introduce RPC tests

The only place we test the interaction between agents and the controller
is in Tempest. These are however 'heavy' tests and are very high level.
There are features that aren't tested in Tempest (Due to no multi node testing
or for other reasons) that have coverage for each individual component but
not for how they interact. In-tree full-stack testing will mitigate this,
but like Tempest, it is too high level as basic RPC interaction can be tested
at a lower level.

The idea is to use the fake Oslo messaging driver (Which is already being
used every where) but to take care not to  mock out critical bits. The fake
driver simply passes messages around in-process without the use of an external
messaging service. The server RPC handlers are already being tested,
so there's no need to test them again. The Oslo messaging driver is not under
test either. So what is being tested? These sort of RPC tests just call an RPC
method from a client, without mocking anything. If the RPC method is expected
to return something, that should be asserted as well.

These tests can catch regressions such as:
https://bugs.launchpad.net/neutron/+bug/1414812

Future work in dependent patches:
* Complete coverage for all RPC methods.
* Mock heavy unit tests that assert that True == True may now be replaced.
* Rolling upgrades cannot be tested via this framework, but via something
  similar to grenade, which Nova always runs with Nova network. I hope
  to look into running it with Neutron as well.

These tests may be run (On your laptop) with:
tox -e functional neutron.tests.functional.api.rpc

This patch includes RPC tests for the agent report_state and
L3 agent methods just so we can be sure the RPC testing framework
provides sufficient functionality for different RPC endpoints.

Change-Id: I7b15f15f69acf2fc4e01e754f6490cdbb37b453e

commit_message:
Identify tenant_id's existence for admin user

When creating networking resource, admin user can override
tenant_id attribute arbitrarily, and we should add a check
to make sure the tenant_id is exist. This is not a common issue,
but may be exist in real environment, for example, admin user
may use an expired tenant_id, which has been deleted, to create
networking resources. To avoid requesting keystone too frequently,
this patch follows metadata agent's cache mechnism, and is
implemented by using @utils.cache_method_results decorator.

Closes-bug: #1200585

Change-Id: If341778e3fe986a3c4f9e97c634d701794dd6727

that the thread must not get monkey patched:
(http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2012-August/000794.html).

options using the configuration options or by simply setting up an
environment variable called `STANDARD_THREADS`.

If the pydev connection fails to be established with the remote debugger an
exception is raised.

environments with IDEs not compatible with patched threads.

commit_message:
Neutron pydevd debugger support

That patch allows a developer to remotely run a pydev debugger and having the
Neutron process connect back to it.

The implementation is similar to the one found in the Keystone or glance
project.

Four configuration options have been added:

    pydev-debug-host <host>. Default is None
    pydev-debug-port <port>. Default is None
    standard-threads (bool): Do not monkey-patch threading system modules.
    no-standard-threads (bool): inverse of --standard-threads. This is the
                             default behavior.

The behavior is enabled if `pydev-debug-host` *and* `pydev-debug-port` are
both not None.

Example:

1. neutron connecting back to pydevd using standard threads

   --pydev-debug-host 1.2.3.4 --pydev-debug-port 12345

2. neutron connection back to pydevd using patched threads

   --pydev-debug-host 1.2.3.4 --pydev-debug-port 12345 --no-standard-threads

If the behavior is enabled, an os.environ variable will be set to indicate
that the thread must not get monkey patched:
(http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2012-August/000794.html).
Then, the pydev connection will be performed by the server right when starting
after reading the configuration.

Minor modifications were required to deal with the multiple calls to the
eventlet monkey patcher in multiple places throughout the Neutron code: a new
module in common has been defined performing the actual patch and
checking if whether or not standard threads are in use to discard thread patch
calls. Calls to eventlet monkey patcher have been changed to leverage this new
module throughout the Neutron code.

`standard-threads` option can be enabled independently of the pydev debug
options using the configuration options or by simply setting up an
environment variable called `STANDARD_THREADS`.

If the pydev connection fails to be established with the remote debugger an
exception is raised.

This patch will allow remote debugging as well as more seamless debugging
environments with IDEs not compatible with patched threads.

Change-Id: Idd4485b405cf0707781aa1250819a2140ee74550
